    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>One in five disk galaxies hosts a nuclear ring. The proposed observations will 
further our understanding of how gas is transformed into stars in a resonance 
driven accretion process. Our goal is to locate GMCs in NGC 3351's robustly star
forming ring using the 230 GHz 12CO(J=2-1) line and determine their resolved 
propertie - CO luminosity, linewidth, and size - on scales of approximately
25 to 200 pc. We will ascertain if the GMCs obey the Larson relations, quantify 
the effects of the local ISM pressure, relate the GMC properties to sites of 
ongoing star formation.</prp:abstract>
